  "texts": [
    "Few-shot learning involves providing the model with a collection of exemplary demonstrations, each comprising both input and desired output, related to the target task.",
    "By exposing the model to these illustrative examples initially, it gains a deeper understanding of human intentions and the criteria for generating desired responses.",
    "Consequently, few-shot learning often results in enhanced performance compared to zero-shot learning.",
    "However, this advantage comes with the trade-off of increased token consumption and the potential challenge of reaching the context length limit, particularly when dealing with lengthy input and output text.",
    "Chain-of-ThoughtOne of the well-known and easily applicable prompt engineering techniques involves adding the phrase \"Think step by step\" to the end of a prompt."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}